Epic written to `/home/stephan/src/FairEmail/docs/epics/3.2-conversation-threading.md`. The document covers:

- **4 threading strategies**: RFC-header-based (always on), Gmail thread index, common-reference, and subject-based fallback — with their priority cascade
- **Thread consolidation**: eager merging when bridging messages arrive
- **Time-bounded lookups**: configurable range (default 128 days) plus fixed 48-hour window for subject-based
- **Conversation view**: auto-expand rules, trashed/draft inclusion, expand/collapse per message
- **Thread-level operations**: move-all and move-sent settings
- **Forward-as-new-thread**: controlling whether forwards break the thread
- **7 open questions** including Outlook Thread-Index readiness, per-account mode, retroactive re-threading, and the FAQ/implementation divergence on subject threading
